-- Ex-EMI CEO readying rival bid: paper
-- 
-- Wed May 23, 2007 8:45am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/05/23/us-emi-fifield-idUSL2321497520070523

 

 LONDON  (Reuters) - Former EMI Group EMI.L Chief Executive Jim Fifield, with the financial backing of private equity firm Corvus Capital, is in the final stages of preparing a 278 pence a share offer for the world's third largest music company, the New York Post reported on Wednesday. 

 The newspaper cited three unnamed sources with knowledge of the offer. EMI's board recommended a 265 pence a share offer from private equity firm Terra Firma on Monday.